title: TypeError
description: The `TypeError` JS object represents an error that occurs when an operation is performed on a value of an inappropriate type, such as calling a method on a non-function object.
content: The object that represents an error when an operation is performed on a value of an incorrect type. This occurs when a value is not of the expected type, such as calling a method on a non-function value or performing operations on incompatible types. It helps in handling type-related issues in code.
